Here are the general tenets of feline tools

Feline tools are a set of tools that are meant to make your mac experience simpler

Here are some of the powerful tools i want to build (+ means complete - means working on)

+ snap: provides rec on how to optimize your computers speed and battery usage and suggests apps to close
+ download: allows you to simply download content from the internet such as images, videos and sites themselves from a simple command
+ scrape: helps you scrape sites in a simpler way
-read: opens given file in a simple and pretty file viewer that is more lightweight than apple preview
+ clean: cleans caches and other things that may be taking unnecessary storage
-log: captures a log of whatever the user wants a log of
-noggin: byok ai that helps you out from your terminal with tools that allow it to gain more context from your computer itself
+ context: provides you context (file directory, where the file is mentioned and things like that) for a given file or directory
-vaccinate: compresses every file within a given directory so that its smaller
+ convert: converts a given file into another file type of the users choice
+ search/browse: a faster version of spotlight search that focuses on apps or files
-schedule: allows you to schedule any of these commands for a certain time
+ lock: locks a certain app or site for a given time to help you focus more
-solve: uses ai to solve any issues you may be having (errors, crashes and other issues)



some of these (like graph and read) will include small and simple popup dialogues or guis that will pop up and then once you clsoe them the command will complete
